==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heartwood
<hw>Heart"wood`</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rt"w⟦oocr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The hard, central part of the trunk of a tree, consisting of the
old and matured wood, and usually differing in color from the outer
layers. It is technically known as <altname>duramen</altname>, and
distinguished from the softer <contr>sapwood</contr> or
<contr>alburnum</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heart-wounded</ent>⟦br⟧
